Let me analyze the target structure and provide a solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 5 main blocks
- It consists of 3 layers (bottom, middle, and top)
- The bottom has a horizontal yellow block
- The middle layer has a vertical green block and two cube blocks (blue on top, red on bottom)
- The top has a horizontal yellow block

Block Selection and Spatial Relationships:
- Bottom horizontal yellow block matches block #11
- Vertical green block matches block #7
- Blue cube matches block #1
- Red cube matches block #3
- Top horizontal yellow block matches block #11

Assembly Order (from bottom to top):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 11 (bottom horizontal yellow block)
    Step2: Move block with index 7 (vertical green block)
    Step3: Move block with index 3 (red cube)
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 11 (top horizontal yellow block)
}

This will create the target structure exactly as shown, with all blocks in their correct orientations and positions.
